
* Can a class inherit multiple classes in java? justify your answer.
* Can a class implement multiple interfaces? justify your answer.


### A class cannot inherit multiple classes in Java because of the ambiguity caused by it. Diamond problem is usually caused by multiple Inheritance.
### Justification: In the Dog class an instance of multiple inheritance was created(Animal and Family), this resulted in an error. Therefore, these proofed that multiple inheritance is not allowed in Java

### A class can implement multiple interfaces in java because it doesn't cause ambiguity.
### Justification: The Interface package(File contained in it) proofs that a class can take multiple interfaces.
